input_str: A century and a half ago today, a pair of Indiana brothers developed a new American artform: the train robbery. On October 6, 1866, the Library of Congress writes that John and Simeon "Sim" Reno got on an Ohio & Mississippi Railroad passenger train near Seymour, a city in Jackson County, Indiana.
